author: Rob Woodfork
title: NFL Week 4 Recap
text:
Home » News » Sports » NFL Week 4 Recap NFL Week 4 Recap By Rob Woodfork October 5, 2015 3:06 am A broken back, an AARP convention, and the Redskins move into a tie for first place. Just another crazy week in the NFL. Eagles 20 Redskins 23 Kirk Cousins told us he’s better and he took a huge step toward proving it by directing a 15-play, 90 yard game winning drive to win the ‘Skins a game they’d usually lose. (Although lately they haven’t; Chip Kelly is 5-2 on the road in-division, with both losses taking place at FedEx Field). Oh, and DeMarco? If you want the ball more , stop counting your money and go get more than 1.6 yards per carry.
